.\" Manpage for asm
.\" Contact jmetelin@student.hive.fi to correct errors or typos.
.TH ASM 8 "14 Sep 2020" "1.0" "asm man page"
.SH ASM
ASM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B     ./asm [-h] [-e] [-d DIR] [-x] [-f FILE] [-l] <sourcefile.s>
.B or: ./asm -z [-d DIR] <sourcefile.cor>
.SH DESCRIPTION
ASM is a program that compiles a champion and translates it from the language it's written in (assembly language) into "Bytecode." Bytecode is a machine language, which is directly interpreted by the virtual machine COREWAR.
.SH OPTIONS
The following options are available:
.TP
.B -h
prints the usage
.TP
.B -e
prints all the errors instead of only the first one
.TP
.B -d DIR
creates the .cor file to the directory DIR
.TP
.B -x
prints the hexdump
.TP
.B -f FILE
names the .cor file FILE
.TP
.B -l
prints memory leaks
.TP
.B -z
disassembles a .cor file to a .s file
.SH SEE ALSO
COREWAR(8)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs EVER. Yes you read that right.
